# AVAudioPlayerNodeCompletionCallbackType.dataRendered

**Case**

A completion handler that indicates the player renders the buffer or file data.

## Declaration

```swift
case dataRendered
```

## Discussion

This case doesn’t account for any signal processing latencies downstream of the player in the engine.

## Completion Handler Cases

- **AVAudioPlayerNodeCompletionCallbackType.dataConsumed**: A completion handler that indicates the player consumes the buffer or file data.
- **AVAudioPlayerNodeCompletionCallbackType.dataPlayedBack**: A completion handler that indicates the player finishes the buffer or file data.
